43// macro for doing simple rewrite
44#define TVM_TRY_REWRITE(SrcExpr, ResExpr) \
45 if ((SrcExpr).Match(ret)) { \
46 return (ResExpr).Eval(); \
47 }
48
49// macro for rewrite + recursively rewrite ResExpr
50#define TVM_TRY_RECURSIVE_REWRITE(SrcExpr, ResExpr) \
51 if ((SrcExpr).Match(ret)) { \
52 return RecursiveRewrite((ResExpr).Eval()); \
53 }
54
55// macro rewrite only if CondExor is true after match.
56#define TVM_TRY_REWRITE_IF(SrcExpr, ResExpr, CondExpr) \
57 if ((SrcExpr).Match(ret) && (CondExpr)) { \
58 return (ResExpr).Eval(); \
59 }
60
61// macro rewrite + recursive_rewrite only if CondExor is true after match.
62#define TVM_TRY_RECURSIVE_REWRITE_IF(SrcExpr, ResExpr, CondExpr) \
63 if ((SrcExpr).Match(ret) && (CondExpr)) { \
64 return RecursiveRewrite((ResExpr).Eval()); \
65 }

67// NOTE for developers:
68//
69// We mainly focus on index expression simplification.
70// Besides the RewriteSimplifier, some cases can be better
71// handled by CanonicalSimplifier.
72//
73
74// try to prove x equals val
75RewriteSimplifier::Impl::CompareResult RewriteSimplifier::Impl::TryCompare(const PrimExpr& x,
76 int64_t val) {
77 PrimExpr diff = this->VisitExpr(x);
78 if (const auto* ptr = diff.as<IntImmNode>()) {
79 if (ptr->value == val) {
80 return kEQ;
81 } else if (ptr->value > val) {
82 return kGT;
83 } else if (ptr->value < val) {
84 return kLT;
85 }
86 }
87 ConstIntBound dbound = analyzer_->const_int_bound(diff);
88 if (dbound->min_value == val && dbound->max_value == val) {
89 return kEQ;
90 }
91 if (dbound->min_value > val) {
92 return kGT;
93 }
94 if (dbound->max_value < val) {
95 return kLT;
96 }
97 if (dbound->min_value >= val) {
98 return kGE;
99 }
100 if (dbound->max_value <= val) {
101 return kLE;
102 }
103 if (val == 0) {
104 ModularSet dmod = analyzer_->modular_set(diff);
105 if (dmod->base != 0) {
106 return kNE;
107 }
108 }
109 return kUnknown;
110}

112void RewriteSimplifier::Impl::Update(const Var& var, const PrimExpr& info, bool can_override) {
113 if (!can_override) {
114 auto it = var_map_.find(var);
115 if (it != var_map_.end()) {
116 ICHECK(ExprDeepEqual()(it->second, info)) << "Trying to update var \'" << var << "\'"
117 << " with a different value: "
118 << "original=" << it->second << ", new=" << info;
119 }
120 }
121 var_map_[var] = info;
122}
123
124PrimExpr RewriteSimplifier::Impl::VisitExpr_(const AddNode* op) {
125 PrimExpr ret = IRMutatorWithAnalyzer::VisitExpr_(op);
126 op = ret.as<AddNode>();
127 PrimExpr const_res = TryConstFold<Add>(op->a, op->b);
128 if (const_res.defined()) return const_res;
129 // Pattern var to match any expression
130 PVar<PrimExpr> x, y, z, b1, b2, s1, s2;
131 // Pattern var match IntImm
132 PVar<IntImm> c1, c2, c3;
133 // Pattern var match FloatImm
134 PVar<FloatImm> c4;
135 // Pattern var for lanes in broadcast and ramp
136 PVar<int> lanes;
137 // Vector rules
138 if (op->dtype.lanes() != 1) {
139 TVM_TRY_REWRITE(ramp(b1, s1, lanes) + ramp(b2, s2, lanes), ramp(b1 + b2, s1 + s2, lanes));
140 TVM_TRY_REWRITE(ramp(b1, s1, lanes) + broadcast(x, lanes), ramp(b1 + x, s1, lanes));
141 TVM_TRY_REWRITE(broadcast(x, lanes) + ramp(b1, s1, lanes), ramp(x + b1, s1, lanes));
142 TVM_TRY_REWRITE(broadcast(x, lanes) + broadcast(y, lanes), broadcast(x + y, lanes));
143 TVM_TRY_REWRITE_IF(x + broadcast(c4, lanes), x, c4.Eval()->value == 0.0f);
144 }
145
146 if (IsIndexType(op->dtype)) {
147 // Index rules
148 // cancelation rules
149 TVM_TRY_REWRITE((x - y) + y, x);
150 TVM_TRY_REWRITE(x + (y - x), y);
151
152 TVM_TRY_REWRITE((x - y) + (y - z), x - z);
153 TVM_TRY_REWRITE((x - y) + (z - x), z - y);
154
155 TVM_TRY_REWRITE(min(x, y - z) + z, min(x + z, y));
156 TVM_TRY_REWRITE(min(x - z, y) + z, min(x, y + z));
157 TVM_TRY_REWRITE(max(x, y - z) + z, max(x + z, y));
158 TVM_TRY_REWRITE(max(x - z, y) + z, max(x, y + z));
159
160 TVM_TRY_REWRITE_IF(min(x, y + z * c1) + z * c2, min(x + z * c2, y),
161 c1.Eval()->value == -c2.Eval()->value);
162 TVM_TRY_REWRITE_IF(max(x, y + z * c1) + z * c2, max(x + z * c2, y),
163 c1.Eval()->value == -c2.Eval()->value);
164 TVM_TRY_REWRITE_IF(min(y + z * c1, x) + z * c2, min(x + z * c2, y),
165 c1.Eval()->value == -c2.Eval()->value);
166 TVM_TRY_REWRITE_IF(max(y + z * c1, x) + z * c2, max(x + z * c2, y),
167 c1.Eval()->value == -c2.Eval()->value);
168
169 TVM_TRY_REWRITE(max(x, y) + min(x, y), x + y);
170 TVM_TRY_REWRITE(min(x, y) + max(x, y), x + y);
171 TVM_TRY_REWRITE(max(x, y) + min(y, x), x + y);
172 TVM_TRY_REWRITE(min(x, y) + max(y, x), x + y);
173
174 TVM_TRY_REWRITE_IF(min(x, y + c1) + c2, min(x + c2, y), c1.Eval()->value == -c2.Eval()->value);
175 TVM_TRY_REWRITE_IF(min(x + c1, y) + c2, min(x, y + c2), c1.Eval()->value == -c2.Eval()->value);
176 TVM_TRY_REWRITE_IF(max(x, y + c1) + c2, max(x + c2, y), c1.Eval()->value == -c2.Eval()->value);
177 TVM_TRY_REWRITE_IF(max(x + c1, y) + c2, max(x, y + c2), c1.Eval()->value == -c2.Eval()->value);
178
179 // constant folding
180 // NOTE: canonicalization might better at this.
181 TVM_TRY_REWRITE((x + c1) + c2, x + (c1 + c2));
182
183 // mul co-efficient folding
184 TVM_TRY_REWRITE(x + x, x * 2);
185 TVM_TRY_REWRITE(x * y + x, x * (y + 1));
186 TVM_TRY_REWRITE(y * x + x, x * (y + 1));
187 TVM_TRY_REWRITE(x + y * x, x * (1 + y));
188 TVM_TRY_REWRITE(x + x * y, x * (1 + y));
189 TVM_TRY_REWRITE(x * y + x * z, x * (y + z));
190 TVM_TRY_REWRITE(y * x + x * z, x * (y + z));
191 TVM_TRY_REWRITE(x * y + z * x, x * (y + z));
192 TVM_TRY_REWRITE(y * x + z * x, x * (y + z));
193
194 // DivMod rules
195 // truc div
196 TVM_TRY_REWRITE(truncdiv(x, c1) * c1 + truncmod(x, c1), x);
197 // floor div
198 TVM_TRY_REWRITE(floordiv(x, y) * y + floormod(x, y), x);
199 TVM_TRY_REWRITE(y * floordiv(x, y) + floormod(x, y), x);
200 TVM_TRY_REWRITE(floormod(x, y) + floordiv(x, y) * y, x);
201 TVM_TRY_REWRITE(floormod(x, y) + y * floordiv(x, y), x);
202
203 TVM_TRY_REWRITE_IF(floordiv(floormod(x, c2) + c1, c2) + floordiv(x, c2), floordiv(x + c1, c2),
204 c2.Eval()->value > 0);
205
206 // canonicalization rule
207 // will try rewrite again after canonicalization.
208 TVM_TRY_RECURSIVE_REWRITE(x + (c1 - y), (x - y) + c1);
209 TVM_TRY_RECURSIVE_REWRITE((c1 - y) + x, (x - y) + c1);
210 TVM_TRY_RECURSIVE_REWRITE(x + c1 + y, (x + y) + c1);
211 TVM_TRY_RECURSIVE_REWRITE(x + (c1 + y), (x + y) + c1);
212 TVM_TRY_RECURSIVE_REWRITE(x + max(y, z), max(y, z) + x);
213 TVM_TRY_RECURSIVE_REWRITE(x + min(y, z), min(y, z) + x);
214
215 // DivMod rules
216 // truc div
217 TVM_TRY_RECURSIVE_REWRITE(truncmod(y, c1) + x * c1, x * c1 + truncmod(y, c1));
218 // floor div
219 TVM_TRY_RECURSIVE_REWRITE(floormod(y, c1) + x * c1, x * c1 + floormod(y, c1));
220 }
221
222 // condition rules.
223 TVM_TRY_REWRITE(select(x, b1, b2) + select(x, s1, s2), select(x, b1 + s1, b2 + s2));
224 // default value
225 return ret;
226}
227
228std::function<void()> RewriteSimplifier::Impl::EnterConstraint(const PrimExpr& constraint) {
229 size_t old_literal_size = literal_constraints_.size();
230 // we will compare the already simplified result with the constraint,
231 // so simplify the constraint as well
232 PrimExpr new_constraint = operator()(constraint);
233 for (const PrimExpr& subconstraint : ExtractConstraints(new_constraint)) {
234 if (SideEffect(subconstraint) <= CallEffectKind::kPure) {
235 literal_constraints_.push_back(subconstraint);
236 // We could apply this during TryMatchLiteralConstraint, but
237 // that would require performing a rewrite of each expression
238 // being checked. This way, we only apply a rewrite for each
239 // constraint being applied.
240 PrimExpr negation;
241 if (subconstraint.dtype().is_bool()) {
242 negation = Not(subconstraint);
243 } else {
244 negation = subconstraint == make_zero(subconstraint.dtype());
245 }
246 negation = operator()(negation);
247 literal_constraints_.push_back(Not(negation));
248 }
249 }
250 size_t new_literal_size = literal_constraints_.size();
251 auto frecover = [old_literal_size, new_literal_size, this]() {
252 ICHECK_EQ(literal_constraints_.size(), new_literal_size);
253 literal_constraints_.resize(old_literal_size);
254 };
255 return frecover;
256}
257
258PrimExpr RewriteSimplifier::Impl::VisitExpr_(const SubNode* op) {
259 PrimExpr ret = IRMutatorWithAnalyzer::VisitExpr_(op);
260 op = ret.as<SubNode>();
261 PrimExpr const_res = TryConstFold<Sub>(op->a, op->b);
262 if (const_res.defined()) return const_res;
263 // Pattern var to match any expression
264 PVar<PrimExpr> x, y, z, b1, b2, s1, s2;
265 // Pattern var match IntImm
266 PVar<IntImm> c1, c2, c3;
267 // Pattern var for lanes in broadcast and ramp
268 PVar<int> lanes;
269 // Vector rules
270 if (op->dtype.lanes() != 1) {
271 TVM_TRY_REWRITE(ramp(b1, s1, lanes) - ramp(b2, s2, lanes), ramp(b1 - b2, s1 - s2, lanes));
272 TVM_TRY_REWRITE(ramp(b1, s1, lanes) - broadcast(x, lanes), ramp(b1 - x, s1, lanes));
273 TVM_TRY_REWRITE(broadcast(x, lanes) - ramp(b1, s1, lanes), ramp(x - b1, 0 - s1, lanes));
274 TVM_TRY_REWRITE(broadcast(x, lanes) - broadcast(y, lanes), broadcast(x - y, lanes));
275 }
276
277 if (IsIndexType(op->dtype)) {
278 // Index rules
279 // cancelation rules
280 TVM_TRY_REWRITE((x + y) - y, x);
281 TVM_TRY_REWRITE((x + y) - x, y);
282 TVM_TRY_REWRITE(x - (y + x), 0 - y);
283 TVM_TRY_REWRITE(x - (x + y), 0 - y);
284
285 TVM_TRY_REWRITE(min(x, y) - x, min(0, y - x));
286 TVM_TRY_REWRITE(min(x, y) - y, min(x - y, 0));
287 TVM_TRY_REWRITE(max(x, y) - x, max(0, y - x));
288 TVM_TRY_REWRITE(max(x, y) - y, max(x - y, 0));
289
290 TVM_TRY_REWRITE(x - max(x, y), min(0, x - y));
291 TVM_TRY_REWRITE(y - max(x, y), min(y - x, 0));
292 TVM_TRY_REWRITE(x - min(x, y), max(0, x - y));
293 TVM_TRY_REWRITE(y - min(x, y), max(y - x, 0));
294
295 // mul co-efficient folding
296 TVM_TRY_REWRITE(x - x, ZeroWithTypeLike(x));
297 TVM_TRY_REWRITE(x * y - x, x * (y - 1));
298 TVM_TRY_REWRITE(y * x - x, x * (y - 1));
299 TVM_TRY_REWRITE(x - y * x, x * (1 - y));
300 TVM_TRY_REWRITE(x - x * y, x * (1 - y));
301 TVM_TRY_REWRITE(x * y - x * z, x * (y - z));
302 TVM_TRY_REWRITE(y * x - x * z, x * (y - z));
303 TVM_TRY_REWRITE(x * y - z * x, x * (y - z));
304 TVM_TRY_REWRITE(y * x - z * x, x * (y - z));
305
306 // constant cancelation
307 TVM_TRY_REWRITE((x + c1) - c2, x + (c1 - c2));
308 TVM_TRY_REWRITE((c1 - x) - (c2 - y), (y - x) + (c1 - c2));
309
310 // cancelization rule involving 4 operands
311 TVM_TRY_REWRITE((x + y) - (x + z), y - z);
312 TVM_TRY_REWRITE((x + y) - (z + x), y - z);
313 TVM_TRY_REWRITE((y + x) - (z + x), y - z);
314 TVM_TRY_REWRITE((y + x) - (x + z), y - z);
315
316 TVM_TRY_REWRITE(min(x + y, z) - x, min(y, z - x));
317 TVM_TRY_REWRITE(min(y + x, z) - x, min(y, z - x));
318 TVM_TRY_REWRITE(min(z, x + y) - x, min(z - x, y));
319 TVM_TRY_REWRITE(min(z, y + x) - x, min(z - x, y));
320
321 TVM_TRY_REWRITE(max(x + y, z) - x, max(y, z - x));
322 TVM_TRY_REWRITE(max(y + x, z) - x, max(y, z - x));
323 TVM_TRY_REWRITE(max(z, x + y) - x, max(z - x, y));
324 TVM_TRY_REWRITE(max(z, y + x) - x, max(z - x, y));
325
326 TVM_TRY_REWRITE(x - min(x + y, z), max(0 - y, x - z));
327 TVM_TRY_REWRITE(x - min(y + x, z), max(0 - y, x - z));
328 TVM_TRY_REWRITE(x - min(z, x + y), max(x - z, 0 - y));
329 TVM_TRY_REWRITE(x - min(z, y + x), max(x - z, 0 - y));
330
331 TVM_TRY_REWRITE(min(x, y) - min(y, x), ZeroWithTypeLike(x));
332 TVM_TRY_REWRITE(max(x, y) - max(y, x), ZeroWithTypeLike(x));
333
334 TVM_TRY_REWRITE_IF(min(b1, b2) - min(s1, s2), b1 - s1,
335 CanProveEqual(((b1 - s1) - (b2 - s2)).Eval(), 0));
336
337 TVM_TRY_REWRITE_IF(min(b1, b2) - min(s1, s2), b1 - s2,
338 CanProveEqual(((b1 - s2) - (b2 - s1)).Eval(), 0));
339 TVM_TRY_REWRITE_IF(max(b1, b2) - max(s1, s2), b1 - s1,
340 CanProveEqual(((b1 - s1) - (b2 - s2)).Eval(), 0));
341 TVM_TRY_REWRITE_IF(max(b1, b2) - max(s1, s2), b1 - s2,
342 CanProveEqual(((b1 - s2) - (b2 - s1)).Eval(), 0));
343
344 // DivMod rules
345 // trucdiv
346 // NOTE: c*(x/c) + x % c == x is true all division mode.
347 TVM_TRY_REWRITE_IF(x - truncdiv(x, c1) * c1, truncmod(x, c1), c1.Eval()->value != 0);
348 TVM_TRY_REWRITE_IF(truncdiv(x, c1) * c1 - x, 0 - truncmod(x, c1), c1.Eval()->value != 0);
349 TVM_TRY_REWRITE_IF(x - (truncdiv(x + y, c1)) * c1, truncmod(x + y, c1) - y,
350 c1.Eval()->value != 0);
351 TVM_TRY_REWRITE_IF((truncdiv(x + y, c1)) * c1 - x, y - truncmod(x + y, c1),
352 c1.Eval()->value != 0);
353 TVM_TRY_REWRITE_IF(x - truncdiv(x - y, c1) * c1, truncmod(x - y, c1) + y,
354 c1.Eval()->value != 0);
355 TVM_TRY_REWRITE_IF(truncdiv(x - y, c1) * c1 - x, 0 - truncmod(x - y, c1) - y,
356 c1.Eval()->value != 0);
357
358 TVM_TRY_REWRITE_IF(
359 x * c2 - truncdiv(x, c1) * c3, truncmod(x, c1) * c2,
360 c1.Eval()->value != 0 && c3.Eval()->value == c1.Eval()->value * c2.Eval()->value);
361 TVM_TRY_REWRITE_IF(
362 truncdiv(x, c1) * c3 - x * c2, 0 - truncmod(x, c1) * c2,
363 c1.Eval()->value != 0 && c3.Eval()->value == c1.Eval()->value * c2.Eval()->value);
364 TVM_TRY_REWRITE_IF(
365 x * c2 - truncdiv(x + y, c1) * c3, (truncmod(x + y, c1) - y) * c2,
366 c1.Eval()->value != 0 && c3.Eval()->value == c1.Eval()->value * c2.Eval()->value);
367 TVM_TRY_REWRITE_IF(
368 truncdiv(x + y, c1) * c3 - x * c2, (y - truncmod(x + y, c1)) * c2,
369 c1.Eval()->value != 0 && c3.Eval()->value == c1.Eval()->value * c2.Eval()->value);
370 TVM_TRY_REWRITE_IF(
371 x * c2 - truncdiv(x - y, c1) * c3, (truncmod(x - y, c1) + y) * c2,
372 c1.Eval()->value != 0 && c3.Eval()->value == c1.Eval()->value * c2.Eval()->value);
373 TVM_TRY_REWRITE_IF(
374 truncdiv(x - y, c1) * c3 - x * c2, (0 - truncmod(x - y, c1) - y) * c2,
375 c1.Eval()->value != 0 && c3.Eval()->value == c1.Eval()->value * c2.Eval()->value);
376
377 // Proof in the case of floordiv, need positive condition.
378 // let x = a * c3 + r
379 // (x + c1) / c3 - x / c3 => (r + c1) / c3
380 // NOTE: the use of floormod(c2, c3) was intentional to simplify the const.
381 TVM_TRY_REWRITE_IF(truncdiv(x + c1, c3) - truncdiv(x + c2, c3),
382 truncdiv(truncmod(x + floormod(c2, c3), c3) + (c1 - c2), c3),
383 CanProveGreaterEqual(x.Eval(), -c2.Eval()->value) &&
384 c1.Eval()->value >= c2.Eval()->value && c3.Eval()->value > 0);
385 TVM_TRY_REWRITE_IF(
386 truncdiv(x + c1, c3) - truncdiv(x, c3), truncdiv(truncmod(x, c3) + c1, c3),
387 CanProveGreaterEqual(x.Eval(), 0) && c1.Eval()->value >= 0 && c3.Eval()->value > 0);
388
389 // floordiv
390 TVM_TRY_REWRITE_IF(x - floordiv(x, c1) * c1, floormod(x, c1), c1.Eval()->value != 0);
391 TVM_TRY_REWRITE_IF(floordiv(x, c1) * c1 - x, 0 - floormod(x, c1), c1.Eval()->value != 0);
392 TVM_TRY_REWRITE_IF(x - floordiv(x + y, c1) * c1, floormod(x + y, c1) - y,
393 c1.Eval()->value != 0);
394 TVM_TRY_REWRITE_IF(floordiv(x + y, c1) * c1 - x, y - floormod(x + y, c1),
395 c1.Eval()->value != 0);
396 TVM_TRY_REWRITE_IF(x - floordiv(x - y, c1) * c1, floormod(x - y, c1) + y,
397 c1.Eval()->value != 0);
398 TVM_TRY_REWRITE_IF(floordiv(x - y, c1) * c1 - x, 0 - floormod(x - y, c1) - y,
399 c1.Eval()->value != 0);
400
401 TVM_TRY_REWRITE_IF(
402 x * c2 - floordiv(x, c1) * c3, floormod(x, c1) * c2,
403 c1.Eval()->value != 0 && c3.Eval()->value == c1.Eval()->value * c2.Eval()->value);
404 TVM_TRY_REWRITE_IF(
405 floordiv(x, c1) * c3 - x * c2, 0 - floormod(x, c1) * c2,
406 c1.Eval()->value != 0 && c3.Eval()->value == c1.Eval()->value * c2.Eval()->value);
407 TVM_TRY_REWRITE_IF(
408 x * c2 - floordiv(x + y, c1) * c3, (floormod(x + y, c1) - y) * c2,
409 c1.Eval()->value != 0 && c3.Eval()->value == c1.Eval()->value * c2.Eval()->value);
410 TVM_TRY_REWRITE_IF(
411 floordiv(x + y, c1) * c3 - x * c2, (y - floormod(x + y, c1)) * c2,
412 c1.Eval()->value != 0 && c3.Eval()->value == c1.Eval()->value * c2.Eval()->value);
413 TVM_TRY_REWRITE_IF(
414 x * c2 - floordiv(x - y, c1) * c3, (floormod(x - y, c1) + y) * c2,
415 c1.Eval()->value != 0 && c3.Eval()->value == c1.Eval()->value * c2.Eval()->value);
416 TVM_TRY_REWRITE_IF(
417 floordiv(x - y, c1) * c3 - x * c2, (0 - floormod(x - y, c1) - y) * c2,
418 c1.Eval()->value != 0 && c3.Eval()->value == c1.Eval()->value * c2.Eval()->value);
419
420 TVM_TRY_REWRITE_IF(floordiv(x + c1, c3) - floordiv(x + c2, c3),
421 floordiv(floormod(x + floormod(c2, c3), c3) + (c1 - c2), c3),
422 c3.Eval()->value > 0);
423 TVM_TRY_REWRITE_IF(floordiv(x + c1, c3) - floordiv(x, c3), floordiv(floormod(x, c3) + c1, c3),
424 c3.Eval()->value > 0);
425
426 // canonicalization rule
427 // will try rewrite again after canonicalization.
428 TVM_TRY_REWRITE(x - c1, x + (0 - c1));
429 TVM_TRY_RECURSIVE_REWRITE((x + c1) - y, (x - y) + c1);
430 TVM_TRY_RECURSIVE_REWRITE(x - (y - z), (x + z) - y);
431 TVM_TRY_RECURSIVE_REWRITE(x - y * c1, x + y * (0 - c1));
432 } else if (op->dtype.is_float()) {
433 // Cancellation rules. Deliberately off of the integer path, to
434 // avoid introducing checks on the side effects for the fast path.
435 TVM_TRY_REWRITE_IF(x - x, ZeroWithTypeLike(x),
436 SideEffect(x.Eval()) <= CallEffectKind::kReadState);
437 TVM_TRY_REWRITE_IF((x + y) - y, x, SideEffect(y.Eval()) <= CallEffectKind::kReadState);
438 TVM_TRY_REWRITE_IF((x + y) - x, y, SideEffect(x.Eval()) <= CallEffectKind::kReadState);
439 TVM_TRY_REWRITE_IF(x - (y + x), 0 - y, SideEffect(x.Eval()) <= CallEffectKind::kReadState);
440 TVM_TRY_REWRITE_IF(x - (x + y), 0 - y, SideEffect(x.Eval()) <= CallEffectKind::kReadState);
441 }
442
443 // condition rules.
444 TVM_TRY_REWRITE(select(x, b1, b2) - select(x, s1, s2), select(x, b1 - s1, b2 - s2));
445 TVM_TRY_REWRITE(select(x, y, z) - z, select(x, y - z, ZeroWithTypeLike(z)));
446 TVM_TRY_REWRITE(select(x, y, z) - y, select(x, ZeroWithTypeLike(y), z - y));
447 return ret;
448}
449
450PrimExpr RewriteSimplifier::Impl::VisitExpr_(const MulNode* op) {
451 PrimExpr ret = IRMutatorWithAnalyzer::VisitExpr_(op);
452 op = ret.as<MulNode>();
453 PrimExpr const_res = TryConstFold<Mul>(op->a, op->b);
454 if (const_res.defined()) return const_res;
455 // Pattern var to match any expression
456 PVar<PrimExpr> x, y, z, b1, b2, s1, s2;
457 // Pattern var match IntImm
458 PVar<IntImm> c1, c2;
459 // Pattern var match FloatImm
460 PVar<FloatImm> c3;
461 // Pattern var for lanes in broadcast and ramp
462 PVar<int> lanes;
463 // Vector rules
464 if (op->dtype.lanes() != 1) {
465 TVM_TRY_REWRITE(broadcast(x, lanes) * broadcast(y, lanes), broadcast(x * y, lanes));
466 TVM_TRY_REWRITE(ramp(b1, s1, lanes) * broadcast(x, lanes), ramp(b1 * x, s1 * x, lanes));
467 TVM_TRY_REWRITE(broadcast(x, lanes) * ramp(b1, s1, lanes), ramp(b1 * x, s1 * x, lanes));
468 TVM_TRY_REWRITE_IF(broadcast(c3, lanes) * x, broadcast(c3, lanes), c3.Eval()->value == 0.0f);
469 }
470
471 if (IsIndexType(op->dtype)) {
472 // constant simplification rule
473 TVM_TRY_REWRITE((x + c1) * c2, x * c2 + c1 * c2);
474 TVM_TRY_REWRITE((x * c1) * c2, x * (c1 * c2));
475 TVM_TRY_REWRITE(min(x, y) * max(x, y), x * y);
476 TVM_TRY_REWRITE(max(x, y) * min(x, y), x * y);
477
478 // Two representations of const*ceildiv(x, c1)
479 TVM_TRY_REWRITE_IF(floordiv(x - floormod(x, c2), c1) * c1, x - floormod(x, c2),
480 c1.Eval()->value == -c2.Eval()->value);
481
482 // canonicalization
483 TVM_TRY_RECURSIVE_REWRITE(x * (c1 * y), (x * y) * c1);
484 TVM_TRY_RECURSIVE_REWRITE(c1 * x, x * c1);
485 TVM_TRY_RECURSIVE_REWRITE_IF((x - y) * c1, (y - x) * (0 - c1), c1.Eval()->value < 0);
486 }
487 return ret;
488}
489
490PrimExpr RewriteSimplifier::Impl::VisitExpr_(const DivNode* op) {
491 PrimExpr ret = IRMutatorWithAnalyzer::VisitExpr_(op);
492 op = ret.as<DivNode>();
493 PrimExpr const_res = TryConstFold<Div>(op->a, op->b);
494 if (const_res.defined()) return const_res;
495 // Pattern var to match any expression
496 PVar<PrimExpr> x, y, z, b1;
497 // Pattern var match IntImm
498 PVar<IntImm> c1, c2, c3;
499 // Pattern var for lanes in broadcast and ramp
500 PVar<int> lanes;
501
502 // x / 2.0 = x * 0.5
503 if (const FloatImmNode* ptr = op->b.as<FloatImmNode>()) {
504 ICHECK(op->dtype.is_float() || op->dtype.is_bfloat16() ||
505 datatype::Registry::Global()->GetTypeRegistered(op->dtype.code()));
506 return op->a * make_const(op->b.dtype(), 1.0 / ptr->value);
507 }
508
509 // Vector rules
510 if (op->dtype.lanes() != 1) {
511 // NOTE: use div as the pattern also works for float.
512 TVM_TRY_REWRITE(div(broadcast(x, lanes), broadcast(y, lanes)), broadcast(div(x, y), lanes));
513 // ramp / bcast
514 if ((div(ramp(b1, c1, lanes), broadcast(c2, lanes))).Match(ret)) {
515 int64_t c1val = c1.Eval()->value;
516 int64_t c2val = c2.Eval()->value;
517 ICHECK(c2val != 0) << "division by zero";
518 if (c1val % c2val == 0) {
519 return ramp(div(b1, c2), div(c1, c2), lanes).Eval();
520 }
521 // If all possible indices in ramp are the same.
522 if (CanProveGreaterEqual(b1.Eval(), 0)) {
523 ModularSet bmod = analyzer_->modular_set(b1.Eval());
524 int64_t ramp_min = bmod->base / c2val;
525 int64_t ramp_max = (bmod->base + (lanes.Eval() - 1) * c1val) / c2val;
526 if (bmod->coeff % c2val == 0 && ramp_min == ramp_max) {
527 return broadcast(div(b1, c2), lanes).Eval();
528 }
529 }
530 }
531 }
532
533 if (IsIndexType(op->dtype)) {
534 // Be-aware of the division rules:
535 // We adopt the default C division uses truncation instead of floordiv.
536 // This means most rules need to check non-negativeness of the operands.
537
538 // TryConstFold doesn't work for negative cases because it is also used by legacy
539 // parts of tvm which still assume euclidean div. In this simplifier we assume that the division
540 // is truncated, so perform const folding again.
541 // NOTE: trunc div required
542 if (truncdiv(c1, c2).Match(ret)) {
543 int64_t c1val = c1.Eval()->value;
544 int64_t c2val = c2.Eval()->value;
545 return make_const(op->dtype, truncdiv(c1val, c2val));
546 }
547
548 // while it is always true for trunc div
549 // restrict to common case(positive div)
550 TVM_TRY_REWRITE_IF(truncdiv(truncdiv(x, c1), c2), truncdiv(x, c1 * c2),
551 c1.Eval()->value > 0 && c2.Eval()->value > 0);
552
553 TVM_TRY_REWRITE_IF(truncdiv(truncdiv(x, c1) + c2, c3), truncdiv(x + c1 * c2, c1 * c3),
554 c1.Eval()->value > 0 && c2.Eval()->value >= 0 && c3.Eval()->value > 0 &&
555 CanProveGreaterEqual(x.Eval(), 0));
556
557 if (truncdiv(x * c1, c2).Match(ret)) {
558 int64_t c1val = c1.Eval()->value;
559 int64_t c2val = c2.Eval()->value;
560 if (c1val > 0 && c2val > 0) {
561 if (c1val % c2val == 0) return (x * truncdiv(c1, c2)).Eval();
562 if (c2val % c1val == 0) return truncdiv(x, truncdiv(c2, c1)).Eval();
563 }
564 }
565
566 TVM_TRY_REWRITE(truncdiv(x, x), OneWithTypeLike(x));
567 TVM_TRY_REWRITE(truncdiv(x * c1, x), c1);
568 TVM_TRY_REWRITE(truncdiv(c1 * x, x), c1);
569
570 // Rules involving 2-operands.
571 TVM_TRY_REWRITE_IF(truncdiv(x * c1 + y, c2), x * truncdiv(c1, c2) + truncdiv(y, c2),
572 c1.Eval()->value >= 0 && c2.Eval()->value > 0 &&
573 c1.Eval()->value % c2.Eval()->value == 0 &&
574 CanProveGreaterEqual(x.Eval(), 0) && CanProveGreaterEqual(y.Eval(), 0));
575
576 TVM_TRY_REWRITE_IF(truncdiv(min(x * c1, y), c2), min(x * truncdiv(c1, c2), truncdiv(y, c2)),
577 c1.Eval()->value >= 0 && c2.Eval()->value > 0 &&
578 c1.Eval()->value % c2.Eval()->value == 0 &&
579 CanProveGreaterEqual(x.Eval(), 0) && CanProveGreaterEqual(y.Eval(), 0));
580
581 TVM_TRY_REWRITE_IF(truncdiv(max(x * c1, y), c2), max(x * truncdiv(c1, c2), truncdiv(y, c2)),
582 c1.Eval()->value >= 0 && c2.Eval()->value > 0 &&
583 c1.Eval()->value % c2.Eval()->value == 0 &&
584 CanProveGreaterEqual(x.Eval(), 0) && CanProveGreaterEqual(y.Eval(), 0));
585
586 TVM_TRY_REWRITE_IF(truncdiv(y + x * c1, c2), truncdiv(y, c2) + x * truncdiv(c1, c2),
587 c1.Eval()->value >= 0 && c2.Eval()->value > 0 &&
588 c1.Eval()->value % c2.Eval()->value == 0 &&
589 CanProveGreaterEqual(x.Eval(), 0) && CanProveGreaterEqual(y.Eval(), 0));
590
591 TVM_TRY_REWRITE_IF(truncdiv(min(y, x * c1), c2), min(truncdiv(y, c2), x * truncdiv(c1, c2)),
592 c1.Eval()->value >= 0 && c2.Eval()->value > 0 &&
593 c1.Eval()->value % c2.Eval()->value == 0 &&
594 CanProveGreaterEqual(x.Eval(), 0) && CanProveGreaterEqual(y.Eval(), 0));
595
596 TVM_TRY_REWRITE_IF(truncdiv(max(y, x * c1), c2), max(truncdiv(y, c2), x * truncdiv(c1, c2)),
597 c1.Eval()->value >= 0 && c2.Eval()->value > 0 &&
598 c1.Eval()->value % c2.Eval()->value == 0 &&
599 CanProveGreaterEqual(x.Eval(), 0) && CanProveGreaterEqual(y.Eval(), 0));
600
601 // Rules involving 3-operands.
602 TVM_TRY_REWRITE_IF(
603 truncdiv(x * c1 + y + z, c2), x * truncdiv(c1, c2) + truncdiv(y + z, c2),
604 c1.Eval()->value >= 0 && c2.Eval()->value > 0 && c1.Eval()->value % c2.Eval()->value == 0 &&
605 CanProveGreaterEqual(x.Eval(), 0) && CanProveGreaterEqual((y + z).Eval(), 0));
606
607 TVM_TRY_REWRITE_IF(
608 truncdiv(x * c1 - y + z, c2), x * truncdiv(c1, c2) + truncdiv(z - y, c2),
609 c1.Eval()->value >= 0 && c2.Eval()->value > 0 && c1.Eval()->value % c2.Eval()->value == 0 &&
610 CanProveGreaterEqual(x.Eval(), 0) && CanProveGreaterEqual((z - y).Eval(), 0));
611
612 TVM_TRY_REWRITE_IF(
613 truncdiv(x * c1 + y - z, c2), x * truncdiv(c1, c2) + truncdiv(y - z, c2),
614 c1.Eval()->value >= 0 && c2.Eval()->value > 0 && c1.Eval()->value % c2.Eval()->value == 0 &&
615 CanProveGreaterEqual(x.Eval(), 0) && CanProveGreaterEqual((y - z).Eval(), 0));
616
617 TVM_TRY_REWRITE_IF(
618 truncdiv(y + x * c1 + z, c2), x * truncdiv(c1, c2) + truncdiv(y + z, c2),
619 c1.Eval()->value > 0 && c2.Eval()->value > 0 && c1.Eval()->value % c2.Eval()->value == 0 &&
620 CanProveGreaterEqual(x.Eval(), 0) && CanProveGreaterEqual((y + z).Eval(), 0));
621
622 TVM_TRY_REWRITE_IF(truncdiv(x + c1, c2), truncdiv(x, c2) + truncdiv(c1, c2),
623 c1.Eval()->value > 0 && c2.Eval()->value > 0 &&
624 c1.Eval()->value % c2.Eval()->value == 0 &&
625 CanProveGreaterEqual(x.Eval(), 0));
626
627 TVM_TRY_REWRITE_IF(truncdiv(x + y, x), truncdiv(y, x) + 1,
628 CanProveGreaterEqual(x.Eval(), 0) && CanProveGreaterEqual(y.Eval(), 0));
629 TVM_TRY_REWRITE_IF(truncdiv(y + x, x), truncdiv(y, x) + 1,
630 CanProveGreaterEqual(x.Eval(), 0) && CanProveGreaterEqual(y.Eval(), 0));
631
632 TVM_TRY_REWRITE_IF(
633 truncdiv((x + y) + z, x), truncdiv(y + z, x) + 1,
634 CanProveGreaterEqual(x.Eval(), 0) && CanProveGreaterEqual((y + z).Eval(), 0));
635 TVM_TRY_REWRITE_IF(
636 truncdiv((y + x) + z, x), truncdiv(y + z, x) + 1,
637 CanProveGreaterEqual(x.Eval(), 0) && CanProveGreaterEqual((y + z).Eval(), 0));
638 TVM_TRY_REWRITE_IF(
639 truncdiv(y + (z + x), x), truncdiv(y + z, x) + 1,
640 CanProveGreaterEqual(x.Eval(), 0) && CanProveGreaterEqual((y + z).Eval(), 0));
641 TVM_TRY_REWRITE_IF(
642 truncdiv(y + (x + z), x), truncdiv(y + z, x) + 1,
643 CanProveGreaterEqual(x.Eval(), 0) && CanProveGreaterEqual((y + z).Eval(), 0));
644
645 TVM_TRY_REWRITE_IF(truncdiv(x * y, y), x,
646 CanProveGreaterEqual(x.Eval(), 0) && CanProveGreaterEqual(y.Eval(), 0));
647 TVM_TRY_REWRITE_IF(truncdiv(y * x, y), x,
648 CanProveGreaterEqual(x.Eval(), 0) && CanProveGreaterEqual(y.Eval(), 0));
649
650 TVM_TRY_REWRITE_IF(truncdiv(x * z + y, z), x + truncdiv(y, z),
651 CanProveGreaterEqual(x.Eval(), 0) && CanProveGreaterEqual(y.Eval(), 0) &&
652 CanProveGreaterEqual(z.Eval(), 0));
653 TVM_TRY_REWRITE_IF(truncdiv(z * x + y, z), x + truncdiv(y, z),
654 CanProveGreaterEqual(x.Eval(), 0) && CanProveGreaterEqual(y.Eval(), 0) &&
655 CanProveGreaterEqual(z.Eval(), 0));
656 TVM_TRY_REWRITE_IF(truncdiv(y + x * z, z), truncdiv(y, z) + x,
657 CanProveGreaterEqual(x.Eval(), 0) && CanProveGreaterEqual(y.Eval(), 0) &&
658 CanProveGreaterEqual(z.Eval(), 0));
659 TVM_TRY_REWRITE_IF(truncdiv(y + z * x, z), truncdiv(y, z) + x,
660 CanProveGreaterEqual(x.Eval(), 0) && CanProveGreaterEqual(y.Eval(), 0) &&
661 CanProveGreaterEqual(z.Eval(), 0));
662 }
663 return ret;
664}
665
666PrimExpr RewriteSimplifier::Impl::VisitExpr_(const ModNode* op) {
667 PrimExpr ret = IRMutatorWithAnalyzer::VisitExpr_(op);
668 op = ret.as<ModNode>();
669 PrimExpr const_res = TryConstFold<Mod>(op->a, op->b);
670 if (const_res.defined()) return const_res;
671
672 // Pattern var to match any expression
673 PVar<PrimExpr> x, y, z, b1;
674 // Pattern var match IntImm
675 PVar<IntImm> c1, c2;
676 // Pattern var for lanes in broadcast and ramp
677 PVar<int> lanes;
678
679 // Vector rules
680 if (op->dtype.lanes() != 1) {
681 TVM_TRY_REWRITE(truncmod(broadcast(x, lanes), broadcast(y, lanes)),
682 broadcast(truncmod(x, y), lanes));
683
684 // ramp % bcast
685 if (truncmod(ramp(b1, c1, lanes), broadcast(c2, lanes)).Match(ret)) {
686 int64_t c1val = c1.Eval()->value;
687 int64_t c2val = c2.Eval()->value;
688 ICHECK(c2val != 0) << "division by zero";
689 if (c1val % c2val == 0) {
690 return broadcast(truncmod(b1, c2), lanes).Eval();
691 }
692 // If all possible indices in ramp are the same.
693 if (CanProveGreaterEqual(b1.Eval(), 0)) {
694 ModularSet bmod = analyzer_->modular_set(b1.Eval());
695 int64_t ramp_min = bmod->base / c2val;
696 int64_t ramp_max = (bmod->base + (lanes.Eval() - 1) * c1val) / c2val;
697 if (bmod->coeff % c2val == 0) {
698 if (ramp_min == ramp_max) {
699 return ramp(truncmod(bmod->base, c2), c1, lanes).Eval();
700 } else {
701 return truncmod(ramp(truncmod(bmod->base, c2), c1, lanes), broadcast(c2, lanes)).Eval();
702 }
703 }
704 }
705 }
706 }
707
708 if (IsIndexType(op->dtype)) {
709 // Be-aware of the division rules:
710 // We adopt the default C division uses truncation instead of floordiv.
711 // This means most rules need to check non-negativeness of the operands.
712 TVM_TRY_REWRITE_IF(truncmod(x * c1, c2), ZeroWithTypeLike(x),
713 c2.Eval()->value != 0 && c1.Eval()->value % c2.Eval()->value == 0);
714
715 TVM_TRY_REWRITE_IF(truncmod(x * c1 + y, c2), truncmod(y, c2),
716 c2.Eval()->value > 0 && c1.Eval()->value % c2.Eval()->value == 0 &&
717 CanProveGreaterEqual((x * c1).Eval(), 0) &&
718 CanProveGreaterEqual(y.Eval(), 0));
719
720 TVM_TRY_REWRITE_IF(truncmod(x + c1, c2), truncmod(x, c2),
721 c2.Eval()->value > 0 && c1.Eval()->value >= 0 &&
722 c1.Eval()->value % c2.Eval()->value == 0 &&
723 CanProveGreaterEqual(x.Eval(), 0));
724
725 TVM_TRY_REWRITE_IF(truncmod(x + y * c1, c2), truncmod(x, c2),
726 c2.Eval()->value > 0 && c1.Eval()->value % c2.Eval()->value == 0 &&
727 CanProveGreaterEqual(x.Eval(), 0) &&
728 CanProveGreaterEqual((y * c1).Eval(), 0));
729
730 // canonicalization: x % c == x % (-c) for truncated division
731 // NOTE: trunc div required
732 TVM_TRY_RECURSIVE_REWRITE_IF(
733 truncmod(x, c1), truncmod(x, PConst<PrimExpr>(make_const(op->dtype, -c1.Eval()->value))),
734 c1.Eval()->value < 0);
735
736 // try modular analysis
737 if (truncmod(x, c1).Match(ret)) {
738 ModularSet mod = analyzer_->modular_set(x.Eval());
739 int64_t c1val = c1.Eval()->value;
740 if (mod->coeff % c1val == 0 && c1val > 0 && CanProveGreaterEqual(x.Eval(), 0)) {
741 return truncmod(mod->base, c1).Eval();
742 }
743 }
744 }
745 return ret;
746}
747
748PrimExpr RewriteSimplifier::Impl::VisitExpr_(const FloorDivNode* op) {
749 PrimExpr ret = IRMutatorWithAnalyzer::VisitExpr_(op);
750 op = ret.as<FloorDivNode>();
751 PrimExpr const_res = TryConstFold<FloorDiv>(op->a, op->b);
752 if (const_res.defined()) return const_res;
753 // Pattern var to match any expression
754 PVar<PrimExpr> x, y, z, b1;
755 // Pattern var match IntImm
756 PVar<IntImm> c1, c2, c3;
757 // Pattern var for lanes in broadcast and ramp
758 PVar<int> lanes;
759
760 // Vector rules
761 if (op->dtype.lanes() != 1) {
762 TVM_TRY_REWRITE(floordiv(broadcast(x, lanes), broadcast(y, lanes)),
763 broadcast(floordiv(x, y), lanes));
764 // ramp // bcast
765 if (floordiv(ramp(b1, c1, lanes), broadcast(c2, lanes)).Match(ret)) {
766 int64_t c1val = c1.Eval()->value;
767 int64_t c2val = c2.Eval()->value;
768 ICHECK(c2val != 0) << "division by zero";
769 if (c1val % c2val == 0) {
770 return ramp(floordiv(b1, c2), floordiv(c1, c2), lanes).Eval();
771 }
772 // If all possible indices in ramp are the same.
773 ModularSet bmod = analyzer_->modular_set(b1.Eval());
774 int64_t ramp_min = floordiv(bmod->base, c2val);
775 int64_t ramp_max = floordiv(bmod->base + (lanes.Eval() - 1) * c1val, c2val);
776 if (ramp_min == ramp_max) {
777 // If b1 can devide c2
778 if (bmod->coeff % c2val == 0) {
779 return broadcast(floordiv(b1, c2), lanes).Eval();
780 }
781 // If all indices can be guaranteed to settle inside a coeff range
782 if (c2val % bmod->coeff == 0 && bmod->base + (lanes.Eval() - 1) * c1val < bmod->coeff) {
783 return broadcast(floordiv(b1, c2), lanes).Eval();
784 }
785 }
786 }
787 }
788
789 if (IsIndexType(op->dtype)) {
790 // Be-aware of the division rules: this is floor division.
791 TVM_TRY_REWRITE_IF(floordiv(floordiv(x, c1), c2), floordiv(x, c1 * c2),
792 c1.Eval()->value > 0 && c2.Eval()->value > 0);
793
794 TVM_TRY_REWRITE_IF(floordiv(floordiv(x, c1) + c2, c3), floordiv(x + c1 * c2, c1 * c3),
795 c1.Eval()->value > 0 && c3.Eval()->value > 0);
796
797 if (floordiv(x * c1 + y, c2).Match(ret) || floordiv(x * c1, c2).Match(ret) ||
798 floordiv(y + x * c1, c2).Match(ret)) {
799 int64_t c1val = c1.Eval()->value;
800 int64_t c2val = c2.Eval()->value;
801 PrimExpr yval = y.EvalOr(Integer(0));
802 if (c2val == 0) return ret;
803
804 // try eliminate residue part
805 PrimExpr residue =
806 floordiv(x.Eval() * floormod(c1.Eval(), c2val) + floormod(yval, c2val), c2val);
807 PrimExpr y_div = CanProveEqual(floordiv(yval, c2val), 0) ? 0 : floordiv(yval, c2val);
808 auto bound = analyzer_->const_int_bound(residue);
809 if (bound.defined() && bound->max_value == bound->min_value) {
810 return x.Eval() * floordiv(c1val, c2.Eval()) + (y_div + Integer(bound->max_value));
811 }
812
813 // try simplify divisor
814 if (c1val > 0 && c2val > 0 && c2val % c1val == 0 &&
815 CanProveLess(floormod(yval, c2val), c1val)) {
816 // assume c2 == a * c1, x == a * x' + b, y = d * c2 + e then
817 // (x * c1 + y) // c2
818 // ==> ((a * x' + b) * c1 + d * a * c1 + e) // (a * c1)
819 // ==> x' + d + (b * c1 + e) // c2
820 // ==> x' + d since 0 <= b * c1 <= (a-1) * c1, 0 <= e < c1
821 // ==> x // (c2 // c1) + (y // c2)
822 return floordiv(x.Eval(), floordiv(c2val, c1val)) + y_div;
823 }
824 }
825
826 TVM_TRY_REWRITE(floordiv(x, x), OneWithTypeLike(x));
827 TVM_TRY_REWRITE(floordiv(x * c1, x), c1);
828 TVM_TRY_REWRITE(floordiv(c1 * x, x), c1);
829
830 // Rules involving 2-operands.
831 TVM_TRY_REWRITE_IF(floordiv(min(x * c1, y), c2), min(x * floordiv(c1, c2), floordiv(y, c2)),
832 c2.Eval()->value > 0 && c1.Eval()->value % c2.Eval()->value == 0);
833
834 TVM_TRY_REWRITE_IF(floordiv(max(x * c1, y), c2), max(x * floordiv(c1, c2), floordiv(y, c2)),
835 c2.Eval()->value > 0 && c1.Eval()->value % c2.Eval()->value == 0);
836
837 TVM_TRY_REWRITE_IF(floordiv(min(y, x * c1), c2), min(floordiv(y, c2), x * floordiv(c1, c2)),
838 c2.Eval()->value > 0 && c1.Eval()->value % c2.Eval()->value == 0);
839
840 TVM_TRY_REWRITE_IF(floordiv(max(y, x * c1), c2), max(floordiv(y, c2), x * floordiv(c1, c2)),
841 c2.Eval()->value > 0 && c1.Eval()->value % c2.Eval()->value == 0);
842
843 // Rules involving 3-operands.
844 TVM_TRY_REWRITE_IF(floordiv(x * c1 + y + z, c2), x * floordiv(c1, c2) + floordiv(y + z, c2),
845 c2.Eval()->value > 0 && c1.Eval()->value % c2.Eval()->value == 0);
846 TVM_TRY_REWRITE_IF(floordiv(x * c1 + y + z, c2), floordiv(x, floordiv(c2, c1)),
847 c1.Eval()->value > 0 && c2.Eval()->value > 0 &&
848 c2.Eval()->value % c1.Eval()->value == 0 &&
849 CanProveEqual(floordiv(y.Eval() + z.Eval(), c1.Eval()), 0));
850
851 TVM_TRY_REWRITE_IF(floordiv(x * c1 - y + z, c2), x * floordiv(c1, c2) + floordiv(z - y, c2),
852 c2.Eval()->value > 0 && c1.Eval()->value % c2.Eval()->value == 0);
853
854 TVM_TRY_REWRITE_IF(floordiv(x * c1 + y - z, c2), x * floordiv(c1, c2) + floordiv(y - z, c2),
855 c2.Eval()->value > 0 && c1.Eval()->value % c2.Eval()->value == 0);
856
857 TVM_TRY_REWRITE_IF(floordiv(y + x * c1 + z, c2), x * floordiv(c1, c2) + floordiv(y + z, c2),
858 c2.Eval()->value > 0 && c1.Eval()->value % c2.Eval()->value == 0);
859
860 TVM_TRY_REWRITE_IF(floordiv(x + c1, c2), floordiv(x, c2) + floordiv(c1, c2),
861 c2.Eval()->value > 0 && c1.Eval()->value % c2.Eval()->value == 0);
862
863 TVM_TRY_REWRITE_IF(floordiv(x * c1, x * c2), floordiv(c1, c2), c2.Eval()->value > 0);
864
865 TVM_TRY_REWRITE_IF(floordiv(x + y, x), floordiv(y, x) + 1, CanProveGreaterEqual(x.Eval(), 0));
866
867 TVM_TRY_REWRITE_IF(floordiv(y + x, x), floordiv(y, x) + 1, CanProveGreaterEqual(x.Eval(), 0));
868
869 TVM_TRY_REWRITE_IF(floordiv((x + y) + z, x), floordiv(y + z, x) + 1,
870 CanProveGreaterEqual(x.Eval(), 0));
871 TVM_TRY_REWRITE_IF(floordiv((y + x) + z, x), floordiv(y + z, x) + 1,
872 CanProveGreaterEqual(x.Eval(), 0));
873 TVM_TRY_REWRITE_IF(floordiv(y + (z + x), x), floordiv(y + z, x) + 1,
874 CanProveGreaterEqual(x.Eval(), 0));
875 TVM_TRY_REWRITE_IF(floordiv(y + (x + z), x), floordiv(y + z, x) + 1,
876 CanProveGreaterEqual(x.Eval(), 0));
877
878 TVM_TRY_REWRITE_IF(floordiv(x * y, y), x, CanProveGreaterEqual(y.Eval(), 0));
879 TVM_TRY_REWRITE_IF(floordiv(y * x, y), x, CanProveGreaterEqual(y.Eval(), 0));
880
881 TVM_TRY_REWRITE_IF(floordiv(x * z + y, z), x + floordiv(y, z),
882 CanProveGreaterEqual(z.Eval(), 0));
883 TVM_TRY_REWRITE_IF(floordiv(z * x + y, z), x + floordiv(y, z),
884 CanProveGreaterEqual(z.Eval(), 0));
885 TVM_TRY_REWRITE_IF(floordiv(y + x * z, z), floordiv(y, z) + x,
886 CanProveGreaterEqual(z.Eval(), 0));
887 TVM_TRY_REWRITE_IF(floordiv(y + z * x, z), floordiv(y, z) + x,
888 CanProveGreaterEqual(z.Eval(), 0));
889
890 TVM_TRY_REWRITE_IF(floordiv(x - floormod(x, c1), c1), floordiv(x, c1), c1.Eval()->value != 0);
891 }
892 return ret;
893}
894
895PrimExpr RewriteSimplifier::Impl::VisitExpr_(const FloorModNode* op) {
896 PrimExpr ret = IRMutatorWithAnalyzer::VisitExpr_(op);
897 op = ret.as<FloorModNode>();
898 PrimExpr const_res = TryConstFold<FloorMod>(op->a, op->b);
899 if (const_res.defined()) return const_res;
900
901 // Pattern var to match any expression
902 PVar<PrimExpr> x, y, z, b1;
903 // Pattern var match IntImm
904 PVar<IntImm> c1, c2;
905 // Pattern var for lanes in broadcast and ramp
906 PVar<int> lanes;
907
908 // Vector rules
909 if (op->dtype.lanes() != 1) {
910 TVM_TRY_REWRITE(floormod(broadcast(x, lanes), broadcast(y, lanes)),
911 broadcast(floormod(x, y), lanes));
912
913 // floormod(ramp, bcast)
914 if (floormod(ramp(b1, c1, lanes), broadcast(c2, lanes)).Match(ret)) {
915 int64_t c1val = c1.Eval()->value;
916 int64_t c2val = c2.Eval()->value;
917 ICHECK(c2val != 0) << "division by zero";
918 if (c1val % c2val == 0) {
919 return broadcast(floormod(b1, c2), lanes).Eval();
920 }
921 // If all possible indices in ramp are the same.
922 ModularSet bmod = analyzer_->modular_set(b1.Eval());
923 int64_t ramp_min = floordiv(bmod->base, c2val);
924 int64_t ramp_max = floordiv(bmod->base + (lanes.Eval() - 1) * c1val, c2val);
925 if (ramp_min == ramp_max) {
926 // If b1 can devide c2
927 if (bmod->coeff % c2val == 0) {
928 return ramp(floormod(bmod->base, c2), c1, lanes).Eval();
929 }
930 // If all indices can be guaranteed to settle inside a coeff range
931 if (c2val % bmod->coeff == 0 && bmod->base + (lanes.Eval() - 1) * c1val < bmod->coeff) {
932 return ramp(floormod(b1, c2), c1, lanes).Eval();
933 }
934 }
935 if (bmod->coeff % c2val == 0) {
936 return floormod(ramp(floormod(bmod->base, c2), c1, lanes), broadcast(c2, lanes)).Eval();
937 }
938 }
939 }
940
941 if (IsIndexType(op->dtype)) {
942 // Be-aware of the division rules: we use floordiv/floormod here
943 TVM_TRY_REWRITE_IF(floormod(x * c1, c2), floormod(x * floormod(c1, c2), c2),
944 c2.Eval()->value != 0);
945
946 TVM_TRY_REWRITE_IF(floormod(x * c1 + y, c2), floormod(x, floordiv(c2, c1)) * c1 + y,
947 c1.Eval()->value > 0 && c2.Eval()->value > 0 &&
948 c2.Eval()->value % c1.Eval()->value == 0 &&
949 CanProveEqual(floordiv(y.Eval(), c1.Eval()), 0));
950
951 TVM_TRY_REWRITE_IF(floormod(x * c1 + y, c2), floormod(x * floormod(c1, c2) + y, c2),
952 c2.Eval()->value > 0);
953
954 TVM_TRY_REWRITE_IF(floormod(x + c1, c2), floormod(x, c2),
955 c2.Eval()->value > 0 && c1.Eval()->value % c2.Eval()->value == 0);
956
957 TVM_TRY_REWRITE_IF(floormod(x + y * c1, c2), floormod(x + y * floormod(c1, c2), c2),
958 c2.Eval()->value > 0);
959
960 TVM_TRY_REWRITE_IF(floormod(x * c1, x * c2), x * floormod(c1, c2), c2.Eval()->value != 0);
961
962 TVM_TRY_REWRITE(floormod(x * y, y), ZeroWithTypeLike(x));
963 TVM_TRY_REWRITE(floormod(y * x, y), ZeroWithTypeLike(y));
964
965 // try modular analysis
966 if (floormod(x, c1).Match(ret)) {
967 ModularSet mod = analyzer_->modular_set(x.Eval());
968 int64_t c1val = c1.Eval()->value;
969 if (mod->coeff % c1val == 0 && c1val > 0) {
970 return floormod(mod->base, c1).Eval();
971 }
972 }
973 }
974 return ret;
975}
976
977PrimExpr RewriteSimplifier::Impl::VisitExpr_(const MinNode* op) {
978 PrimExpr ret = IRMutatorWithAnalyzer::VisitExpr_(op);
979 op = ret.as<MinNode>();
980 PrimExpr const_res = TryConstFold<Min>(op->a, op->b);
981 if (const_res.defined()) return const_res;
982
983 // Pattern var to match any expression
984 PVar<PrimExpr> x, y, z, s1, s2;
985 // Pattern var match IntImm
986 PVar<IntImm> c1, c2;
987 PVar<int> lanes;
988
989 // vector rule
990 if (op->dtype.lanes() != 1) {
991 TVM_TRY_REWRITE(min(broadcast(x, lanes), broadcast(y, lanes)), broadcast(min(x, y), lanes));
992 TVM_TRY_REWRITE(min(min(x, broadcast(y, lanes)), broadcast(z, lanes)),
993 min(x, broadcast(min(y, z), lanes)));
994 }
995 if (IsIndexType(op->dtype)) {
996 TVM_TRY_REWRITE(min(x, x), x);
997
998 // constant int bound
999 ConstIntBound a_bound = analyzer_->const_int_bound(op->a);
1000 ConstIntBound b_bound = analyzer_->const_int_bound(op->b);
1001 if (a_bound->max_value <= b_bound->min_value) {
1002 return op->a;
1003 }
1004 if (b_bound->max_value <= a_bound->min_value) {
1005 return op->b;
1006 }
1007
1008 // constant comparison
1009 if (min(x + c1, x + c2).Match(ret)) {
1010 if (c1.Eval()->value < c2.Eval()->value) {
1011 return (x + c1).Eval();
1012 } else {
1013 return (x + c2).Eval();
1014 }
1015 }
1016 if (min(x + c1, x).Match(ret) || min(x, x + c1).Match(ret)) {
1017 if (c1.Eval()->value < 0) {
1018 return (x + c1).Eval();
1019 } else {
1020 return x.Eval();
1021 }
1022 }
1023 if (min(c1 - x, c2 - x).Match(ret)) {
1024 if (c1.Eval()->value < c2.Eval()->value) {
1025 return (c1 - x).Eval();
1026 } else {
1027 return (c2 - x).Eval();
1028 }
1029 }
1030
1031 // DivMod rules
1032 // Divide up rounding: truc div
1033 // NOTE: trucdiv(x, y) >= floordiv(x, y)
1034 TVM_TRY_REWRITE_IF(min(truncdiv(x + c1, c2) * c2, x), x,
1035 c2.Eval()->value > 0 && c1.Eval()->value + 1 == c2.Eval()->value);
1036 TVM_TRY_REWRITE_IF(min(truncdiv(x + c1, c2) * c2, max(x, c2)), max(x, c2),
1037 c2.Eval()->value > 0 && c1.Eval()->value + 1 == c2.Eval()->value &&
1038 CanProveGreaterEqual(x.Eval(), 0));
1039
1040 TVM_TRY_REWRITE_IF(min(x, truncdiv(x + c1, c2) * c2), x,
1041 c2.Eval()->value > 0 && c1.Eval()->value + 1 == c2.Eval()->value);
1042 TVM_TRY_REWRITE_IF(min(max(x, c2), truncdiv(x + c1, c2) * c2), max(x, c2),
1043 c2.Eval()->value > 0 && c1.Eval()->value + 1 == c2.Eval()->value &&
1044 CanProveGreaterEqual(x.Eval(), 0));
1045
1046 // Divide up rounding: floor div
1047 TVM_TRY_REWRITE_IF(min(floordiv(x + c1, c2) * c2, x), x,
1048 c2.Eval()->value > 0 && c1.Eval()->value + 1 == c2.Eval()->value);
1049 TVM_TRY_REWRITE_IF(min(floordiv(x + c1, c2) * c2, max(x, c2)), max(x, c2),
1050 c2.Eval()->value > 0 && c1.Eval()->value + 1 == c2.Eval()->value);
1051
1052 TVM_TRY_REWRITE_IF(min(x, floordiv(x + c1, c2) * c2), x,
1053 c2.Eval()->value > 0 && c1.Eval()->value + 1 == c2.Eval()->value);
1054 TVM_TRY_REWRITE_IF(min(max(x, c2), floordiv(x + c1, c2) * c2), max(x, c2),
1055 c2.Eval()->value > 0 && c1.Eval()->value + 1 == c2.Eval()->value);
1056
1057 TVM_TRY_REWRITE_IF(min(x, floordiv(x, c2) * c2), floordiv(x, c2) * c2, c2.Eval()->value > 0);
1058 TVM_TRY_REWRITE_IF(min(floordiv(x, c2) * c2, x), floordiv(x, c2) * c2, c2.Eval()->value > 0);
1059
1060 TVM_TRY_REWRITE(min(max(x, y), min(x, y)), min(x, y));
1061 TVM_TRY_REWRITE(min(max(x, y), min(y, x)), min(x, y));
1062 TVM_TRY_REWRITE(min(min(x, y), max(x, y)), min(x, y));
1063 TVM_TRY_REWRITE(min(min(x, y), max(y, x)), min(x, y));
1064
1065 TVM_TRY_REWRITE(min(max(x, y), x), x);
1066 TVM_TRY_REWRITE(min(max(x, y), y), y);
1067 TVM_TRY_REWRITE(min(min(x, y), x), min(x, y));
1068 TVM_TRY_REWRITE(min(min(x, y), y), min(x, y));
1069
1070 TVM_TRY_REWRITE(min(x, max(x, y)), x);
1071 TVM_TRY_REWRITE(min(y, max(x, y)), y);
1072 TVM_TRY_REWRITE(min(x, min(x, y)), min(x, y));
1073 TVM_TRY_REWRITE(min(y, min(x, y)), min(x, y));
1074
1075 TVM_TRY_REWRITE(min(min(min(x, y), z), y), min(min(x, y), z));
1076 TVM_TRY_REWRITE(min(min(min(min(x, y), z), s1), y), min(min(min(x, y), z), s1));
1077 TVM_TRY_REWRITE(min(min(min(min(min(x, y), z), s1), s2), y),
1078 min(min(min(min(x, y), z), s1), s2));
1079
1080 TVM_TRY_REWRITE(min(max(x, y), max(x, z)), max(min(y, z), x));
1081 TVM_TRY_REWRITE(min(max(x, y), max(z, x)), max(min(y, z), x));
1082 TVM_TRY_REWRITE(min(max(y, x), max(x, z)), max(min(y, z), x));
1083 TVM_TRY_REWRITE(min(max(y, x), max(z, x)), max(min(y, z), x));
1084
1085 TVM_TRY_REWRITE(min(min(x, y), min(x, z)), min(min(y, z), x));
1086 TVM_TRY_REWRITE(min(min(x, y), min(z, x)), min(min(y, z), x));
1087 TVM_TRY_REWRITE(min(min(y, x), min(x, z)), min(min(y, z), x));
1088 TVM_TRY_REWRITE(min(min(y, x), min(z, x)), min(min(y, z), x));
1089
1090 TVM_TRY_REWRITE(min(y + x, z + x), min(y, z) + x);
1091 TVM_TRY_REWRITE(min(y + x, x + z), min(y, z) + x);
1092 TVM_TRY_REWRITE(min(x + y, x + z), min(y, z) + x);
1093 TVM_TRY_REWRITE(min(x + y, z + x), min(y, z) + x);
1094
1095 // sub distribution
1096 TVM_TRY_REWRITE(min(y - x, z - x), min(y, z) - x);
1097 TVM_TRY_REWRITE(min(x - y, x - z), x - max(y, z));
1098
1099 // constant folding rule.
1100 TVM_TRY_REWRITE(min(min(x, c1), c2), min(x, min(c1, c2)));
1101
1102 // scaling rule
1103 if (min(truncdiv(x, c1), truncdiv(y, c1)).Match(ret)) {
1104 if (c1.Eval()->value > 0) {
1105 return truncdiv(min(x, y), c1).Eval();
1106 } else {
1107 return truncdiv(max(x, y), c1).Eval();
1108 }
1109 }
1110 if (min(floordiv(x, c1), floordiv(y, c1)).Match(ret)) {
1111 if (c1.Eval()->value > 0) {
1112 return floordiv(min(x, y), c1).Eval();
1113 } else {
1114 return floordiv(max(x, y), c1).Eval();
1115 }
1116 }
1117 if (min(x * c1, y * c1).Match(ret)) {
1118 if (c1.Eval()->value > 0) {
1119 return (min(x, y) * c1).Eval();
1120 } else {
1121 return (max(x, y) * c1).Eval();
1122 }
1123 }
1124 if (min(x * c1, c2).Match(ret)) {
1125 int64_t c1val = c1.Eval()->value;
1126 int64_t c2val = c2.Eval()->value;
1127 if (c1val == 0) {
1128 return c2val < 0 ? c2.Eval() : c1.Eval();
1129 }
1130 if (c2val % c1val == 0) {
1131 if (c1val > 0) {
1132 return (min(x, c2val / c1val) * c1val).Eval();
1133 } else {
1134 return (max(x, c2val / c1val) * c1val).Eval();
1135 }
1136 }
1137 }
1138
1139 // canonicalization
1140 TVM_TRY_RECURSIVE_REWRITE(min(min(x, c1), y), min(min(x, y), c1));
1141 TVM_TRY_RECURSIVE_REWRITE_IF(min(c1 - x, c2), c1 - max(x, c1 - c2), c2.Eval()->value != 0);
1142 }
1143
1144 // condition rules.
1145 TVM_TRY_REWRITE(min(select(x, y, z), select(x, s1, s2)), select(x, min(y, s1), min(z, s2)));
1146 return ret;
1147}
1148
1149PrimExpr RewriteSimplifier::Impl::VisitExpr_(const MaxNode* op) {
1150 PrimExpr ret = IRMutatorWithAnalyzer::VisitExpr_(op);
1151 op = ret.as<MaxNode>();
1152 PrimExpr const_res = TryConstFold<Max>(op->a, op->b);
1153 if (const_res.defined()) return const_res;
1154
1155 // Pattern var to match any expression
1156 PVar<PrimExpr> x, y, z, s1, s2;
1157 // Pattern var match IntImm
1158 PVar<IntImm> c1, c2;
1159 PVar<int> lanes;
1160
1161 // vector rule
1162 if (op->dtype.lanes() != 1) {
1163 TVM_TRY_REWRITE(max(broadcast(x, lanes), broadcast(y, lanes)), broadcast(max(x, y), lanes));
1164 TVM_TRY_REWRITE(max(max(x, broadcast(y, lanes)), broadcast(z, lanes)),
1165 max(x, broadcast(max(y, z), lanes)));
1166 }
1167 if (IsIndexType(op->dtype)) {
1168 TVM_TRY_REWRITE(max(x, x), x);
1169
1170 // constant int bound
1171 ConstIntBound a_bound = analyzer_->const_int_bound(op->a);
1172 ConstIntBound b_bound = analyzer_->const_int_bound(op->b);
1173 if (a_bound->min_value >= b_bound->max_value) {
1174 return op->a;
1175 }
1176 if (b_bound->min_value >= a_bound->max_value) {
1177 return op->b;
1178 }
1179
1180 // constant comparison
1181 if (max(x + c1, x + c2).Match(ret)) {
1182 if (c1.Eval()->value > c2.Eval()->value) {
1183 return (x + c1).Eval();
1184 } else {
1185 return (x + c2).Eval();
1186 }
1187 }
1188 if (max(x + c1, x).Match(ret) || max(x, x + c1).Match(ret)) {
1189 if (c1.Eval()->value > 0) {
1190 return (x + c1).Eval();
1191 } else {
1192 return x.Eval();
1193 }
1194 }
1195 if (max(c1 - x, c2 - x).Match(ret)) {
1196 if (c1.Eval()->value > c2.Eval()->value) {
1197 return (c1 - x).Eval();
1198 } else {
1199 return (c2 - x).Eval();
1200 }
1201 }
1202
1203 // DivMod rules
1204 // Divide up rounding: truc div
1205 // NOTE: trucdiv(x, y) >= floordiv(x, y)
1206 TVM_TRY_REWRITE_IF(max(truncdiv(x + c1, c2) * c2, x), truncdiv(x + c1, c2) * c2,
1207 c2.Eval()->value > 0 && c1.Eval()->value + 1 == c2.Eval()->value);
1208 TVM_TRY_REWRITE_IF(max(x, truncdiv(x + c1, c2) * c2), truncdiv(x + c1, c2) * c2,
1209 c2.Eval()->value > 0 && c1.Eval()->value + 1 == c2.Eval()->value);
1210
1211 // Divide up rounding: floor div
1212 TVM_TRY_REWRITE_IF(max(floordiv(x + c1, c2) * c2, x), floordiv(x + c1, c2) * c2,
1213 c2.Eval()->value > 0 && c1.Eval()->value + 1 == c2.Eval()->value);
1214 TVM_TRY_REWRITE_IF(max(x, floordiv(x + c1, c2) * c2), floordiv(x + c1, c2) * c2,
1215 c2.Eval()->value > 0 && c1.Eval()->value + 1 == c2.Eval()->value);
1216
1217 TVM_TRY_REWRITE_IF(max(floordiv(x, c2) * c2, x), x, c2.Eval()->value > 0);
1218 TVM_TRY_REWRITE_IF(max(x, floordiv(x, c2) * c2), x, c2.Eval()->value > 0);
1219
1220 TVM_TRY_REWRITE(max(min(x, y), max(x, y)), max(x, y));
1221 TVM_TRY_REWRITE(max(min(x, y), max(y, x)), max(x, y));
1222 TVM_TRY_REWRITE(max(max(x, y), min(x, y)), max(x, y));
1223 TVM_TRY_REWRITE(max(max(x, y), min(y, x)), max(x, y));
1224
1225 TVM_TRY_REWRITE(max(min(x, y), x), x);
1226 TVM_TRY_REWRITE(max(min(x, y), y), y);
1227 TVM_TRY_REWRITE(max(max(x, y), x), max(x, y));
1228 TVM_TRY_REWRITE(max(max(x, y), y), max(x, y));
1229
1230 TVM_TRY_REWRITE(max(x, min(x, y)), x);
1231 TVM_TRY_REWRITE(max(y, min(x, y)), y);
1232 TVM_TRY_REWRITE(max(x, max(x, y)), max(x, y));
1233 TVM_TRY_REWRITE(max(y, max(x, y)), max(x, y));
1234
1235 TVM_TRY_REWRITE(max(max(max(x, y), z), y), max(max(x, y), z));
1236 TVM_TRY_REWRITE(max(max(max(max(x, y), z), s1), y), max(max(max(x, y), z), s1));
1237 TVM_TRY_REWRITE(max(max(max(max(max(x, y), z), s1), s2), y),
1238 max(max(max(max(x, y), z), s1), s2));
1239
1240 // max/max cancelation
1241 TVM_TRY_REWRITE(max(max(x, y), max(x, z)), max(max(y, z), x));
1242 TVM_TRY_REWRITE(max(max(x, y), max(z, x)), max(max(y, z), x));
1243 TVM_TRY_REWRITE(max(max(y, x), max(x, z)), max(max(y, z), x));
1244 TVM_TRY_REWRITE(max(max(y, x), max(z, x)), max(max(y, z), x));
1245
1246 // max/min distribution
1247 TVM_TRY_REWRITE(max(min(x, y), min(x, z)), min(max(y, z), x));
1248 TVM_TRY_REWRITE(max(min(x, y), min(z, x)), min(max(y, z), x));
1249 TVM_TRY_REWRITE(max(min(y, x), min(x, z)), min(max(y, z), x));
1250 TVM_TRY_REWRITE(max(min(y, x), min(z, x)), min(max(y, z), x));
1251
1252 // add distribution
1253 TVM_TRY_REWRITE(max(y + x, z + x), max(y, z) + x);
1254 TVM_TRY_REWRITE(max(y + x, x + z), max(y, z) + x);
1255 TVM_TRY_REWRITE(max(x + y, x + z), max(y, z) + x);
1256 TVM_TRY_REWRITE(max(x + y, z + x), max(y, z) + x);
1257
1258 // sub distribution
1259 TVM_TRY_REWRITE(max(y - x, z - x), max(y, z) - x);
1260 TVM_TRY_REWRITE(max(x - y, x - z), x - min(y, z));
1261
1262 // constant folding rule.
1263 TVM_TRY_REWRITE(max(max(x, c1), c2), max(x, max(c1, c2)));
1264
1265 // scaling rule
1266 if (max(truncdiv(x, c1), truncdiv(y, c1)).Match(ret)) {
1267 if (c1.Eval()->value > 0) {
1268 return truncdiv(max(x, y), c1).Eval();
1269 } else {
1270 return truncdiv(min(x, y), c1).Eval();
1271 }
1272 }
1273 if (max(floordiv(x, c1), floordiv(y, c1)).Match(ret)) {
1274 if (c1.Eval()->value > 0) {
1275 return floordiv(max(x, y), c1).Eval();
1276 } else {
1277 return floordiv(min(x, y), c1).Eval();
1278 }
1279 }
1280 if (max(x * c1, y * c1).Match(ret)) {
1281 if (c1.Eval()->value > 0) {
1282 return (max(x, y) * c1).Eval();
1283 } else {
1284 return (min(x, y) * c1).Eval();
1285 }
1286 }
1287 if (max(x * c1, c2).Match(ret)) {
1288 int64_t c1val = c1.Eval()->value;
1289 int64_t c2val = c2.Eval()->value;
1290 if (c1val == 0) {
1291 return c2val > 0 ? c2.Eval() : c1.Eval();
1292 }
1293 if (c2val % c1val == 0) {
1294 if (c1val > 0) {
1295 return (max(x, c2val / c1val) * c1val).Eval();
1296 } else {
1297 return (min(x, c2val / c1val) * c1val).Eval();
1298 }
1299 }
1300 }
1301
1302 // canonicalization
1303 TVM_TRY_RECURSIVE_REWRITE(max(max(x, c1), y), max(max(x, y), c1));
1304 TVM_TRY_RECURSIVE_REWRITE_IF(max(c1 - x, c2), c1 - min(x, c1 - c2), c2.Eval()->value != 0);
1305 }
1306
1307 // condition rules.
1308 TVM_TRY_REWRITE(max(select(x, y, z), select(x, s1, s2)), select(x, max(y, s1), max(z, s2)));
1309 return ret;
1310}
1311
1312Optional<PrimExpr> RewriteSimplifier::Impl::TryMatchLiteralConstraint(const PrimExpr& expr) const {
1313 PrimExpr negation = Not(expr);
1314
1315 ExprDeepEqual expr_equal;
1316 for (const auto& constraint : literal_constraints_) {
1317 if (expr_equal(constraint, expr)) {
1318 return make_const(expr->dtype, true);
1319 }
1320 if (expr_equal(constraint, negation)) {
1321 return make_const(expr->dtype, false);
1322 }
1323 }
1324 return NullOpt;
1325}

1327PrimExpr RewriteSimplifier::Impl::VisitExpr_(const EQNode* op) {
1328 PrimExpr ret = IRMutatorWithAnalyzer::VisitExpr_(op);
1329 op = ret.as<EQNode>();
1330 PrimExpr const_res = TryConstFold<EQ>(op->a, op->b);
1331 if (const_res.defined()) return const_res;
1332 if (auto match = TryMatchLiteralConstraint(ret)) return match.value();
1333
1334 // Pattern var to match any expression
1335 PVar<PrimExpr> x, y;
1336 // Pattern var match IntImm
1337 PVar<IntImm> c1;
1338 PVar<int> lanes;
1339
1340 // vector rule
1341 if (op->dtype.lanes() != 1) {
1342 TVM_TRY_REWRITE(broadcast(x, lanes) == broadcast(y, lanes), broadcast(x == y, lanes));
1343 }
1344
1345 if (IsIndexType(op->a.dtype())) {
1346 CompareResult result = TryCompare(op->a - op->b, 0);
1347 if (result == kEQ) {
1348 return make_const(op->dtype, true);
1349 } else if (result == kNE || result == kGT || result == kLT) {
1350 return make_const(op->dtype, false);
1351 }
1352 TVM_TRY_REWRITE(x - c1 == 0, x == c1);
1353 TVM_TRY_REWRITE(c1 - x == 0, x == c1);
1354 TVM_TRY_REWRITE(x + c1 == 0, x == 0 - c1);
1355 TVM_TRY_REWRITE(x * y == 0, x == 0 || y == 0);
1356 }
1357 return ret;
1358}

1372PrimExpr RewriteSimplifier::Impl::VisitExpr_(const GENode* op) {
1373 return this->VisitExpr(Not(op->a < op->b));
1374}
1375
1376PrimExpr RewriteSimplifier::Impl::VisitExpr_(const LTNode* op) {
1377 PrimExpr ret = IRMutatorWithAnalyzer::VisitExpr_(op);
1378 op = ret.as<LTNode>();
1379 PrimExpr const_res = TryConstFold<LT>(op->a, op->b);
1380 if (const_res.defined()) return const_res;
1381 if (auto match = TryMatchLiteralConstraint(ret)) return match.value();
1382
1383 // Pattern var to match any expression
1384 PVar<PrimExpr> x, y, z, s1, s2;
1385 // Pattern var match IntImm
1386 PVar<IntImm> c1, c2;
1387 PVar<int> lanes;
1388
1389 // vector rule
1390 if (op->dtype.lanes() != 1) {
1391 TVM_TRY_REWRITE(broadcast(x, lanes) < broadcast(y, lanes), broadcast(x < y, lanes));
1392 TVM_TRY_REWRITE(ramp(x, s1, lanes) < ramp(y, s1, lanes), broadcast(x < y, lanes));
1393 }
1394
1395 if (IsIndexType(op->a.dtype())) {
1396 CompareResult result = TryCompare(op->a - op->b, 0);
1397 if (result == kLT) {
1398 return make_const(op->dtype, true);
1399 }
1400 if (result == kEQ || result == kGT || result == kGE) {
1401 return make_const(op->dtype, false);
1402 }
1403
1404 // clang-format off
1405 TVM_TRY_REWRITE(x + y < x + z, y < z);
1406 TVM_TRY_REWRITE(x + y < z + x, y < z);
1407 TVM_TRY_REWRITE(y + x < x + z, y < z);
1408 TVM_TRY_REWRITE(y + x < z + x, y < z);
1409 TVM_TRY_REWRITE(y - x < z - x, y < z);
1410 TVM_TRY_REWRITE(x - y < x - z, z < y);
1411
1412 TVM_TRY_REWRITE(x < x + z, 0 < z);
1413 TVM_TRY_REWRITE(x < z + x, 0 < z);
1414 TVM_TRY_REWRITE(x < x - z, z < 0);
1415 TVM_TRY_REWRITE(c1 < x + c2, c1 - c2 < x);
1416 TVM_TRY_REWRITE(c1 < c2 - x, x < c2 - c1);
1417
1418 TVM_TRY_REWRITE_IF(x * c1 < y * c1, x < y, c1.Eval()->value > 0);
1419 TVM_TRY_REWRITE_IF(x * c1 < y * c1, y < x, c1.Eval()->value < 0);
1420
1421 // constant cancelation: only need to make use of one mod
1422 // truc div
1423 TVM_TRY_REWRITE_IF(x * c2 < c1,
1424 x < truncdiv(c1 - 1, c2) + 1, c1.Eval()->value > 0 && c2.Eval()->value > 0);
1425 // NOTE: trunc div required
1426 TVM_TRY_REWRITE_IF(x * c2 < c1, x < truncdiv(c1, c2),
1427 c1.Eval()->value <= 0 && c2.Eval()->value > 0);
1428 // NOTE: trunc div required (euclidean is ok too, floored is not)
1429 TVM_TRY_REWRITE_IF(x * c2 < c1, truncdiv(c1 - 1, c2) - 1 < x, c1.Eval()->value > 0 &&
1430 c2.Eval()->value < 0);
1431 // NOTE: trunc div required (floored is ok too, euclidean is not)
1432 TVM_TRY_REWRITE_IF(x * c2 < c1, truncdiv(c1, c2) < x,
1433 c1.Eval()->value <= 0 && c2.Eval()->value < 0);
1434 // NOTE: trunc div required
1435 TVM_TRY_REWRITE_IF(c1 < x * c2, truncdiv(c1 + 1, c2) - 1 < x,
1436 c1.Eval()->value < 0 && c2.Eval()->value > 0);
1437 TVM_TRY_REWRITE_IF(c1 < x * c2, truncdiv(c1, c2) < x,
1438 c1.Eval()->value >= 0 && c2.Eval()->value > 0);
1439 // NOTE: trunc div required (floored is ok too, euclidean is not)
1440 TVM_TRY_REWRITE_IF(c1 < x * c2, x < truncdiv(c1 + 1, c2) + 1,
1441 c1.Eval()->value < 0 && c2.Eval()->value < 0);
1442 // NOTE: trunc div required (euclidean is ok too, floored is not)
1443 TVM_TRY_REWRITE_IF(c1 < x * c2, x < truncdiv(c1, c2),
1444 c1.Eval()->value >= 0 && c2.Eval()->value < 0);
1445 // DivMod rules
1446 // trucdiv
1447 TVM_TRY_REWRITE_IF(truncdiv(x, c1) < c2,
1448 x<c1 * c2, c1.Eval()->value> 0 && c2.Eval()->value > 0);
1449 // NOTE: trunc div required
1450 TVM_TRY_REWRITE_IF(truncdiv(x, c1) < c2,
1451 x<c1*(c2 - 1) + 1, c1.Eval()->value> 0 && c2.Eval()->value <= 0);
1452
1453 TVM_TRY_REWRITE_IF(c1 < truncdiv(x, c2), (c1 + 1) * c2 - 1 < x,
1454 c1.Eval()->value >= 0 && c2.Eval()->value > 0);
1455 // NOTE: trunc div required
1456 TVM_TRY_REWRITE_IF(c1 < truncdiv(x, c2), c1 * c2 < x,
1457 c1.Eval()->value < 0 && c2.Eval()->value > 0);
1458
1459 // invariance for any div mod: x - (x / c1) * c1 == x % c1
1460 TVM_TRY_REWRITE_IF(truncdiv(x, c1) * c1 < x, 0 < truncmod(x, c1), c1.Eval()->value > 0);
1461 TVM_TRY_REWRITE_IF(truncdiv(x, c1) * c1 < x + y,
1462 0 < truncmod(x, c1) + y, c1.Eval()->value > 0);
1463 TVM_TRY_REWRITE_IF(truncdiv(x, c1) * c1 < x - y,
1464 y < truncmod(x, c1), c1.Eval()->value > 0);
1465
1466 TVM_TRY_REWRITE_IF(truncdiv(x + c2, c1) * c1 < x,
1467 c2 < truncmod(x + c2, c1), c1.Eval()->value > 0);
1468 TVM_TRY_REWRITE_IF(truncdiv(x + c2, c1) * c1 < x + y,
1469 c2 < truncmod(x + c2, c1) + y, c1.Eval()->value > 0);
1470 TVM_TRY_REWRITE_IF(truncdiv(x + c2, c1) * c1 < x - y,
1471 y < truncmod(x + c2, c1) + (0 - c2), c1.Eval()->value > 0);
1472
1473 // floordiv
1474 TVM_TRY_REWRITE_IF(floordiv(x, c1) < c2, x < c1 * c2, c1.Eval()->value > 0);
1475 TVM_TRY_REWRITE_IF(c1 < floordiv(x, c2), (c1 + 1) * c2 - 1 < x, c2.Eval()->value > 0);
1476
1477 TVM_TRY_REWRITE_IF(floordiv(x, c1) * c1 < x, 0 < floormod(x, c1), c1.Eval()->value > 0);
1478 TVM_TRY_REWRITE_IF(floordiv(x, c1) * c1 < x + y,
1479 0 < floormod(x, c1) + y, c1.Eval()->value > 0);
1480 TVM_TRY_REWRITE_IF(floordiv(x, c1) * c1 < x - y,
1481 y < floormod(x, c1), c1.Eval()->value > 0);
1482 TVM_TRY_REWRITE_IF(floordiv(x + c2, c1) * c1 < x,
1483 c2 < floormod(x + c2, c1), c1.Eval()->value > 0);
1484 TVM_TRY_REWRITE_IF(floordiv(x + c2, c1) * c1 < x + y,
1485 c2 < floormod(x + c2, c1) + y, c1.Eval()->value > 0);
1486 TVM_TRY_REWRITE_IF(floordiv(x + c2, c1) * c1 < x - y,
1487 y < floormod(x + c2, c1) + (0 - c2), c1.Eval()->value > 0);
1488
1489 // canonicalization rule
1490 TVM_TRY_RECURSIVE_REWRITE(min(x, y) < z, x < z || y < z);
1491 TVM_TRY_RECURSIVE_REWRITE(max(x, y) < z, x < z && y < z);
1492 TVM_TRY_RECURSIVE_REWRITE(z < min(x, y), z < x && z < y);
1493 TVM_TRY_RECURSIVE_REWRITE(z < max(x, y), z < x || z < y);
1494
1495 TVM_TRY_RECURSIVE_REWRITE(x < c1 - y, x + y < c1);
1496 TVM_TRY_RECURSIVE_REWRITE(x < c1 + y, x - y < c1);
1497 TVM_TRY_RECURSIVE_REWRITE(c1 - y < x, c1 < x + y);
1498 TVM_TRY_RECURSIVE_REWRITE(c1 + y < x, c1 < x - y);
1499
1500 TVM_TRY_RECURSIVE_REWRITE(x + c1 < c2, x < c2 - c1);
1501 TVM_TRY_RECURSIVE_REWRITE(x - c1 < c2, x < c2 + c1);
1502 TVM_TRY_REWRITE(x - c1 < 0, x < c1);
1503 // clang-format on
1504 }
1505 return ret;
1506}

1508PrimExpr RewriteSimplifier::Impl::VisitExpr_(const NotNode* op) {
1509 PrimExpr ret = IRMutatorWithAnalyzer::VisitExpr_(op);
1510 op = ret.as<NotNode>();
1511 PrimExpr const_res = TryConstFold<Not>(op->a);
1512 if (const_res.defined()) return const_res;
1513 if (auto match = TryMatchLiteralConstraint(ret)) return match.value();
1514
1515 // Pattern var to match any expression
1516 PVar<PrimExpr> x, y;
1517 PVar<int> lanes;
1518 if (op->dtype.lanes() != 1) {
1519 TVM_TRY_REWRITE(!broadcast(x, lanes), broadcast(!x, lanes));
1520 }
1521
1522 TVM_TRY_REWRITE(!(!x), x);
1523 TVM_TRY_REWRITE(!(x <= y), y < x);
1524 TVM_TRY_REWRITE(!(x >= y), x < y);
1525 TVM_TRY_REWRITE(!(x < y), y <= x);
1526 TVM_TRY_REWRITE(!(x > y), x <= y);
1527 TVM_TRY_REWRITE(!(x == y), x != y);
1528 TVM_TRY_REWRITE(!(x != y), x == y);
1529 TVM_TRY_RECURSIVE_REWRITE(!(x || y), (!x) && (!y));
1530 TVM_TRY_RECURSIVE_REWRITE(!(x && y), (!x) || (!y));
1531 return ret;
1532}

1534PrimExpr RewriteSimplifier::Impl::VisitExpr_(const AndNode* op) {
1535 PrimExpr ret = IRMutatorWithAnalyzer::VisitExpr_(op);
1536 op = ret.as<AndNode>();
1537 PrimExpr const_res = TryConstFold<And>(op->a, op->b);
1538 if (const_res.defined()) return const_res;
1539 if (auto match = TryMatchLiteralConstraint(ret)) return match.value();
1540
1541 // Pattern var to match any expression
1542 PVar<PrimExpr> x, y;
1543 // Pattern var match IntImm
1544 PVar<IntImm> c1, c2;
1545 PVar<int> lanes;
1546
1547 if (op->dtype.lanes() != 1) {
1548 TVM_TRY_REWRITE(broadcast(x, lanes) && broadcast(y, lanes), broadcast(x && y, lanes));
1549 }
1550
1551 auto cfalse = PConst<PrimExpr>(make_const(op->dtype, false));
1552 TVM_TRY_REWRITE(x == y && x != y, cfalse);
1553 TVM_TRY_REWRITE(x != y && x == y, cfalse);
1554 TVM_TRY_REWRITE(x && !x, cfalse);
1555 TVM_TRY_REWRITE(x <= y && y < x, cfalse);
1556 TVM_TRY_REWRITE(y < x && x <= y, cfalse);
1557
1558 TVM_TRY_REWRITE_IF(x < c1 && c2 < x, cfalse, c2.Eval()->value + 1 >= c1.Eval()->value);
1559 TVM_TRY_REWRITE_IF(c2 < x && x < c1, cfalse, c2.Eval()->value + 1 >= c1.Eval()->value);
1560
1561 TVM_TRY_REWRITE_IF(x < c1 && c2 <= x, cfalse, c2.Eval()->value >= c1.Eval()->value);
1562 TVM_TRY_REWRITE_IF(c2 <= x && x < c1, cfalse, c2.Eval()->value >= c1.Eval()->value);
1563 TVM_TRY_REWRITE_IF(x <= c1 && c2 < x, cfalse, c2.Eval()->value >= c1.Eval()->value);
1564 TVM_TRY_REWRITE_IF(c2 < x && x <= c1, cfalse, c2.Eval()->value >= c1.Eval()->value);
1565
1566 TVM_TRY_REWRITE_IF(x <= c1 && c2 <= x, cfalse, c2.Eval()->value > c1.Eval()->value);
1567 TVM_TRY_REWRITE_IF(c2 <= x && x <= c1, cfalse, c2.Eval()->value > c1.Eval()->value);
1568
1569 TVM_TRY_REWRITE(x == c1 && x != c2, x == c1 && c1 != c2);
1570 TVM_TRY_REWRITE(x != c2 && x == c1, x == c1 && c1 != c2);
1571 return ret;
1572}

1574PrimExpr RewriteSimplifier::Impl::VisitExpr_(const OrNode* op) {
1575 PrimExpr ret = IRMutatorWithAnalyzer::VisitExpr_(op);
1576 op = ret.as<OrNode>();
1577 PrimExpr const_res = TryConstFold<Or>(op->a, op->b);
1578 if (const_res.defined()) return const_res;
1579 if (auto match = TryMatchLiteralConstraint(ret)) return match.value();
1580
1581 // Pattern var to match any expression
1582 PVar<PrimExpr> x, y;
1583 // Pattern var match IntImm
1584 PVar<IntImm> c1, c2;
1585 PVar<int> lanes;
1586
1587 if (op->dtype.lanes() != 1) {
1588 TVM_TRY_REWRITE(broadcast(x, lanes) || broadcast(y, lanes), broadcast(x || y, lanes));
1589 }
1590
1591 auto ctrue = PConst<PrimExpr>(make_const(op->dtype, true));
1592
1593 TVM_TRY_REWRITE(x == y || x != y, ctrue);
1594 TVM_TRY_REWRITE(x != y || x == y, ctrue);
1595 TVM_TRY_REWRITE(x || !x, ctrue);
1596 TVM_TRY_REWRITE(x <= y || y < x, ctrue);
1597 TVM_TRY_REWRITE(y < x || x <= y, ctrue);
1598
1599 TVM_TRY_REWRITE_IF(x < c1 || c2 < x, ctrue, c2.Eval()->value < c1.Eval()->value);
1600 TVM_TRY_REWRITE_IF(c2 < x || x < c1, ctrue, c2.Eval()->value < c1.Eval()->value);
1601
1602 TVM_TRY_REWRITE_IF(x <= c1 || c2 < x, ctrue, c2.Eval()->value <= c1.Eval()->value);
1603 TVM_TRY_REWRITE_IF(c2 < x || x <= c1, ctrue, c2.Eval()->value <= c1.Eval()->value);
1604 TVM_TRY_REWRITE_IF(x < c1 || c2 <= x, ctrue, c2.Eval()->value <= c1.Eval()->value);
1605 TVM_TRY_REWRITE_IF(c2 <= x || x < c1, ctrue, c2.Eval()->value <= c1.Eval()->value);
1606
1607 TVM_TRY_REWRITE_IF(x <= c1 || c2 <= x, ctrue, c2.Eval()->value <= c1.Eval()->value + 1);
1608 TVM_TRY_REWRITE_IF(c2 <= x || x <= c1, ctrue, c2.Eval()->value <= c1.Eval()->value + 1);
1609
1610 TVM_TRY_REWRITE(x != c1 || x == c2, x != c1 || c1 == c2);
1611 TVM_TRY_REWRITE(x == c2 || x != c1, x != c1 || c1 == c2);
1612 return ret;
1613}

1615PrimExpr RewriteSimplifier::Impl::VisitExpr_(const SelectNode* op) {

1617 op = ret.as<SelectNode>();
1618 if (op == nullptr) return ret;

1625PrimExpr RewriteSimplifier::Impl::VisitExpr_(const CallNode* op) {
1626 // add condition context to if_then_else
1627 PrimExpr ret = IRMutatorWithAnalyzer::VisitExpr_(op);
1628 op = ret.as<CallNode>();
1629 if (op == nullptr) return ret;
1630
1631 if (op->op.same_as(tir::builtin::likely()) && is_const_int(op->args[0])) {
1632 return op->args[0];
1633 } else if (op->op.same_as(tir::builtin::shift_right())) {
1634 if (op->args[0].as<IntImmNode>() && op->args[1].as<IntImmNode>()) {
1635 // the operator overload will eagerly constant fold.
1636 return op->args[0] >> op->args[1];
1637 }
1638 } else if (op->op.same_as(tir::builtin::shift_left())) {
1639 if (op->args[0].as<IntImmNode>() && op->args[1].as<IntImmNode>()) {
1640 // the operator overload will eagerly constant fold.
1641 return op->args[0] << op->args[1];
1642 }
1643 } else if (op->op.same_as(Op::Get("tir.ceil"))) {
1644 PrimExpr ceil_arg = op->args[0];
1645 if (auto arg_int = op->args[0].as<IntImmNode>()) {
1646 return cast(op->dtype, IntImm(arg_int->dtype, arg_int->value));
1647 } else if (auto arg_float = ceil_arg.as<FloatImmNode>()) {
1648 return cast(op->dtype, FloatImm(arg_float->dtype, std::ceil(arg_float->value)));
1649 } else if (auto arg_call = ceil_arg.as<CallNode>()) {
1650 // ceil(log2(cast(n,"float64"))) is used as the implementation of
1651 // topi.math.ceil_log2, and appears in iteration bounds.
1652 if (arg_call->op.same_as(Op::Get("tir.log2"))) {
1653 PrimExpr log_arg = arg_call->args[0];
1654 if (auto as_float = log_arg.as<FloatImmNode>()) {
1655 // ceil(log2(n)) can be simplified, and should produce the
1656 // same integer result regardless of the target's rounding
1657 // conventions.
1658 return FloatImm(op->dtype, std::ceil(std::log2(as_float->value)));
1659 }
1660 }
1661 }
1662 }
1663
1664 if (op->op.same_as(tir::builtin::likely())) {
1665 // Cases such as for (i, 0, bound) {if (likely(iter_var < bound)) { .. } }
1666 if (auto match = TryMatchLiteralConstraint(op->args[0])) {
1667 return match.value();
1668 }
1669 }
1670
1671 return ret;
1672}

1675 Var var = GetRef<Var>(op);
1676 if (op->dtype == DataType::Bool()) {

1678 return match.value();

1695bool RewriteSimplifier::Impl::CanInlineLet(const LetNode* op) {
1696 // Only inline trivial bindings to avoid deep expression explosion
1697 // when we need let to construct complicated expressions.
1698 if (is_const_number(op->value)) return true;
1699 if (op->value.as<VarNode>()) return true;
1700 return false;
1701}
1702
1703PrimExpr RewriteSimplifier::Impl::VisitExpr_(const LetNode* op) {
1704 PrimExpr value = this->VisitExpr(op->value);
1705 if (CanInlineLet(op)) {
1706 // it is fine to discard the let binding
1707 // because the value will always be inlined in the simplifier.
1708 analyzer_->Bind(op->var, value);
1709 return this->VisitExpr(op->body);
1710 }
1711 PrimExpr body = this->VisitExpr(op->body);
1712 if (value.same_as(op->value) && body.same_as(op->body)) {
1713 return GetRef<PrimExpr>(op);
1714 } else {
1715 return Let(op->var, value, body);
1716 }
1717}
1718
1719PrimExpr RewriteSimplifier::operator()(const PrimExpr& expr) {
1720 // Run simplification in post order
1721 PrimExpr res = expr;
1722 int max_iter = 2;
1723 for (int i = 0; i < max_iter; ++i) {
1724 PrimExpr new_expr = impl_->operator()(res);
1725 if (new_expr.same_as(res)) return res;
1726 res = new_expr;
1727 }
1728 return res;
1729}

1732 impl_->Update(var, info, allow_override);
1733}
